title: Romanian protesters light up huge rally with phone torches - BBC News
text:
Media playback is unsupported on your device Romanian protesters light up huge rally with phone torches 6 February 2017 Last updated at 11:55 GMT 
Up to 500,000 protesters shone torches on their phones at an anti-corruption rally in the capital Bucharest, lighting up Victory Square. 
The demonstration came despite the government revoking a controversial decree which would have shielded many politicians from prosecution for corruption. Read more
